author: @FatihKarakuzu
text: Heay sentdex, i read the comments and just found 1 that says to get rid of comments. I think thats a great idea but not because of the opening and closing of comments.   Code in general is like a hard rulebook but comments are way more "messy" than code. In comments is to much variation cause of natural language. If you would got rid of it then you would have mostly hard ruled language except of variablenames.   I think thats way more effective to learn and train a NN like this.   Love the videos you do so keep up man.
